title: Dean King - Skeletons on the Zahara (rip-oop)
description:
Skeletons of the Zahara: A True Story of Survival

Dean King 2004

Narrated by Michael Prichard, Books on Tape, Unabridged, 2004

----

This shipwreck-and-survival saga occurred in 1815 in the wind-tortured territory of the modern Western Sahara and was promptly written down by American brigantine captain James Riley. So popular it appeared in six different editions, Riley's account is revived here with the benefit of author King's journey to retrace, in part, the 800-mile desert trek of Riley and his shipwrecked crew.
